ajority%20court%20could%20hand%20Trump%20a%20massive%20legal%20win%20with%20their%20ruling%20if%20they%20offer%20a%20sweeping%20decision%20that%20affirms%20immunity%20for%20the%20former%20president's%20actions%2C%20as%20his%20lawyers%20have%20argued%2C%20analysts%20and%20legal%20experts%20say%20it's%20more%20likely%20he'll%20be%20offered%20a%20minor%20victory%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20may%20not%20issue%20a%20final%20ruling%20on%20immunity%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20clue%2C%20hidden%20in%20a%202009%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.minnesotalawreview.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2012%2F01%2FKavanaugh_MLR.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elegal%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20written%20by%20Trump-appointed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkavanaugh-address-student-loan-forgiveness-lawsuit-state-standing-debt-relief-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJustice%20Brett%20Kavanaugh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20could%20indicate%20how%20the%20conservative%20judge%20may%20decide%20in%20this%20case.%20And%20as%20Kavanaugh%20is%20relatively%20moderate%20compared%20to%20the%20court's%20other%20right-leaning%20justices%2C%20his%2015-year-old%20analysis%20may%20offer%20insight%20into%20how%20the%20other%20Republican-appointed%20justices%20are%20looking%20at%20the%20matter%20before%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20presidency%20free%20of%20distractions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20article%2C%20published%20in%20the%20Minnesota%20Law%20Review%20in%202009%2C%20when%20he%20was%20working%20as%20a%20US%20Circuit%20Judge%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EKavanaugh%20argues%20that%20the%20public%20grossly%20underestimates%20the%20difficulty%20of%20the%20President's%20job%20and%20that%20anyone%20elected%20to%20hold%20the%20office%20should%20%26quot%3Bbe%20able%20to%20focus%20on%20his%20never-ending%20tasks%20with%20as%20few%20distractions%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20includes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-key-cases-civil-criminal-investigations-lawsuits-updates-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecriminal%20prosecution%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20while%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20point%20is%20not%20to%20put%20the%20President%20above%20the%20law%20or%20to%20eliminate%20checks%20on%20the%20President%2C%20but%20simply%20to%20defer%20litigation%20and%20investigations%20until%20the%20President%20is%20out%20of%20office%2C%26quot%3B%20Kavanaugh%20wrote%2C%20arguing%20in%20favor%20of%20deferring%20criminal%20and%20civil%20prosecutions%20against%20sitting%20presidents%20accused%20of%20wrongdoing%20to%20ensure%20they%20can%20efficiently%20carry%20out%20the%20responsibilities%20of%20office.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOne%20might%20contend%20that%20the%20country%20needs%20a%20check%20against%20a%20bad-behaving%20or%20law-breaking%20president%2C%20Kavanaugh%20acknowledges%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Constitution%20already%20provides%20that%20check.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20President%20does%20something%20dastardly%2C%20the%20impeachment%20process%20is%20available.%20No%20single%20prosecutor%2C%20judge%2C%20or%20jury%20should%20be%20able%20to%20accomplish%20what%20the%20Constitution%20assigns%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%26quot%3B%20Kavanaugh%20wrote.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BMoreover%2C%20an%20impeached%20and%20removed%20President%20is%20still%20subject%20to%20criminal%20prosecution%20afterwards.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20President's%20job%20is%20difficult%20enough%20as%20is%2C%20Kavanaugh%20argued%2C%20so%20he%20shouldn't%20be%20burdened%20by%20prosecution%20attempts%20while%20in%20office%2C%20especially%20since%20there%20are%20avenues%20to%20remove%20him%20from%20office%20if%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20writing%2C%20Kavanaugh%20noted%20he%20didn't%20always%20feel%20this%20way%2C%20so%20it's%20possible%20he%20may%20have%20changed%20his%20mind%20on%20this%20topic%20in%20the%20intervening%20years.%20Still%2C%20a%20question%20remains%20about%20his%20intent%20when%20using%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaw-professor-grades-trump-lawyer-immunity-argument-assassinate-political-rival-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpeached%20and%20removed%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20if%20that%20could%20impact%20how%20he%20rules%20on%20Trump's%20claims%20of%20sweeping%20immunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-trump-immunity-case-january-6-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20lawyers%20have%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20could%20only%20be%20held%20criminally%20liable%20for%20actions%20taken%20while%20in%20office%20if%20he%20was%20impeached%20and%20removed%20by%20Congress%20for%20the%20behavior%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Entin%2C%20a%20retired%20constitutional%20law%20professor%20at%20Case%20Western%20Reserve%20University%20who%20clerked%20for%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-justices-self-pardon-trump-immunity-hearing-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20Justice%20Ruth%20Bader%20Ginsburg%20while%20she%20was%20in%20the%20DC%20Circuit%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%2C%20based%20on%20his%20writing%2C%20Kavanaugh%20might%20not%20agree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20read%20that%20as%20saying%20that%20Kavanaugh%20would%20agree%20with%20the%20Trump%20argument%20about%20you%20have%20to%20be%20impeached%20and%20removed%20before%20you%20can%20be%20prosecuted%2C%26quot%3B%20Entin%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20read%20that%20part%20of%20the%20article%20as%20saying%20that%20the%20President%20is%20not%20subject%20to%20indictment%20and%20prosecution%20while%20in%20office.%20That%20is%20a%20position%20that%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20has%20maintained%20under%20both%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20administrations%20alike.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20real%20factors%20SCOTUS%20is%20weighing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEntin%20said%20that%20instead%20of%20deciding%20whether%20impeachment%20and%20removal%20are%20required%20to%20quash%20claims%20of%20immunity%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EKavanaugh%20and%20the%20other%20conservative%20justices%20might%20more%20likely%20be%20considering%20whether%20to%20draw%20a%20hard-line%20rule%20about%20when%20immunity%20applies%20or%20establish%20a%20general%20standard%20by%20which%20these%20types%20of%20claims%20can%20be%20measured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%2C%20in%20the%20oral%20arguments%2C%20were%20talking%20about%20potential%20future%20prosecutions%20might%20be%20trying%20to%20draw%20a%20bright%20line%20which%20says%2C%20'okay%2C%20these%20sorts%20of%20activities%20might%20be%20subject%20to%20prosecution%2C%20but%20other%20things%20the%20President%20will%20have%20immunity%2C'%26quot%3B%20Entin%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20conservative%20justices%20tended%20to%20be%20more%20focused%20on%20future%20applications%20of%20the%20decision%20rather%20than%20crafting%20a%20ruling%20based%20on%20the%20specific%20set%20of%20facts%20at%20hand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20what%20drives%20their%20decision%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20he%20doesn't%20rule%20out%20partisan%20ideology%20as%20a%20factor%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0Entin%20said%20it's%20unlikely%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20resolve%20the%20question%20of%20presidential%20immunity%20in%20this%20case%20completely.%20He%20expects%20the%20Justices%20to%20kick%20the%20decision%20back%20down%20to%20the%20lower%20courts%20in%20what%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-trump-january-6-trial-timing-delay-2024-election-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20victory%2C%20but%20not%20a%20landslide%2C%20for%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20sense%20is%20that%20we%20are%20probably%20going%20to%20get%20something%20that%20looks%20like