%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20centenarian%2C%20Patricia%2C%20had%20booked%20the%20seat%20for%20an%20adult%20but%20laughed%20off%20the%20incident%20with%20the%20confused%20cabin%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatricia%20told%20the%20BBC%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20funny%20that%20they%20thought%20I%20was%20only%20a%20little%20child%20and%20I'm%20an%20old%20lady!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20she%20said%20it%20was%20not%20the%20first%20time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-airlines-new-collection-premium-amenities-bedding-front-row-suite-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Airlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20mistaken%20her%20for%20a%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatricia%2C%20who%20flies%20every%20year%20to%20visit%20family%2C%20said%20that%20the%20airline's%20booking%20system%20cannot%20seem%20to%20process%20the%20fact%20that%20she%20was%20born%20in%201922%20rather%20than%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20daughter%20made%20the%20reservation%20online%20for%20the%20ticket%2C%20and%20the%20computer%20at%20the%20airport%20thought%20my%20birth%20date%20was%202022%20and%20not%201922%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20previous%20trip%2C%20the%20glitch%20meant%20that%20airport%20staff%20met%20her%20after%20a%20flight%20without%20a%20pre-arranged%20wheelchair%2C%20thinking%20that%20they%20would%20just%20transport%20a%20baby%20through%20the%20terminal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20same%20thing%20happened%20last%20year%20and%20they%20were%20also%20expecting%20a%20child%20and%20not%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Patricia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20to%20wait%20on%20the%20plane%20until%20all%20other%20passengers%20had%20disembarked%20while%20they%20brought%20her%20a%20wheelchair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20like%20them%20to%20fix%20the%20computer%20as%20my%20poor%20daughter%20had%20to%20carry%20all%20our%20luggage%20and%20apparel%20almost%20a%20mile%20from%20one%20gate%20to%20the%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20Airlines%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirlines%20are%20increasingly%20adopting%20automation%20across%20their%20systems%20to%20make%20operations%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20passengers%20mostly%20embrace%20the%20convenience%20that%20technology%20brings%20to%20their%20travel%20experiences.%20In%20the%20latest%20annual%20American%20Customer%20Satisfaction%20Index%2C%20app%20services%2C%20ease%20of%20making%20reservations%2C%20and%20airlines'%20websites%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmuse.insider.com%2Fstory%2F6628c827d541c16b9708245d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20factors%20that%20customers%20were%20most%20satisfied%20with%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20traveling%20with%20US%20airlines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20technology%20generally%20makes%20operations%20smoother%20and%20more%20efficient%2C%20glitches%20routinely%20pop%20up%2C%20often%20affecting%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-chaos-disabled-passengers-says-pilot-helped-off-flight-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evulnerable%20passengers%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20special%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EErrors%20with%20technology%20have%20also%20caused%20serious%20disruption%20to%20global%20travel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20a%20glitch%20in%20the%20UK's%20national%20automatic%20flight-planning%20system%20last%20August%20left%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-traffic-control-problems-delays-travel-chaos-holiday-weekend-uk-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eair%20traffic%20control%20staff%20processing%20flights%20by%20hand%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20issue%20led%20to%20more%20than%201%2C500%20flight%20cancellations%20across%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%2012%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-airlines-flights-pilots-scheduled-glitch-labor-shortage-travel-disruption-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20Airlines%20flights%20were%20left%20without%20pilots%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20glitch%20allowed%20them%20to%20drop%20assignments.%20The%20airline%20had%20to%20offer%20pilots%20triple%20pay%20to%20cover%20the%20fallout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-airlines-booking-system-glitch-mistaking-passenger-baby-planes-tech-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714386134000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662f59d8ec0c696569fe8aca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-airlines-booking-system-glitch-mistaking-passenger-baby-planes-tech-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThe%20computer%20at%20the%20airport%20thought%20my%20birth%20date%20was%202022%20and%20not%201922%2C%26quot%3B%20Patricia%20told%20a%20BBC%20reporter%20on%20the%20same%20flight.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pthompson%40insider.com%20(Polly%20Thompson)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A28%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-airlines-booking-system-glitch-mistaking-passenger-baby-planes-tech-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20Many%20Hours%20Of%20Physical%20Activity%20For%20Good%20Health%3F%20What%20Study%20Says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFor%20optimal%20health%2C%20a%20person's%20ideal%20day%20should%20include%20more%20than%20four%20hours%20of%20physical%20activity%20involving%20exercise%20of%20light%2C%20moderate%20or%20vigourous%20intensity%2C%20and%20at%20least%20eight%20hours%20of%20sleep%2C%20new%20research%20has%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELight-intensity%20activity%20could%20range%20from%20doing%20chores%20to%20making%20dinner%2C%20whereas%20moderate%20and%20vigourous%20exercise%20involve%20more%20intentional%20movement%20such%20as%20a%20brisk%20walk%20or%20a%20gym%20workout%2C%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ideal%20daily%20routine%20should%20also%20include%20six%20hours%20of%20sitting%20and%20five%20hours%20of%20standing%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20international%20team%2C%20led%20by%20Swinburne%20University%20of%20Technology%2C%20Australia%2C%20analysed%20the%20behaviour%20of%20more%20than%202%2C000%20people%20within%20a%2024-hour%20day%20to%20determine%20the%20right%20mix%20of%20time%20spent%20sitting%2C%20sleeping%2C%20standing%20and%20being%20physically%20active%20for%20desirable%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20breakdown%20encompasses%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20health%20markers%20and%20converges%20on%20the%2024%20hours%20associated%20with%20overall%20optimal%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Christian%20Brakenridge%2C%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20Urban%20Transitions%2C%20Swinburne%20University%20of%20Technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20different%20health%20markers%2C%20from%20waist%20circumference%20to%20fasting%20glucose%2C%20there%20would%20be%20different%20levels%20for%20each%20behaviour%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20Brakenridge%2C%20also%20the%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20Diabetologia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20switching%20time%20spent%20sitting%20with%20more%20time%20being%20physically%20active%20or%20performing%20light-intensity%20movements%20was%20associated%20with%20more%20beneficial%20blood%20glucose%20levels%20in%20individuals%20having%20diabetes%20than%20those%20without%20the%20condition%2C%20the%20researchers%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20findings%20also%20acknowledged%20how%20a%20certain%20activity%20replacing%20another%20could%20impact%20an%20individual's%20whole%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSleeping%20may%20be%20detrimental%20to%20health%20if%20it%20replaces%20exercise%20time%2C%20but%20beneficial%20if%20it%20replaces%20sedentary%20behaviour%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20Brakenridge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20even%20as%20exercising%20is%20more%20beneficial%2C%20time%20use%20has%20to%20be%20realistic%20and%20balanced%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20may%20advocate%20for%20more%20time%20exercising%2C%20though%20it's%20not%20feasible%20to%20have%2010%20hours%20of%20exercise%20and%20zero%20hours%20of%20sedentary%20behaviour%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researcher%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20findings%20applied%20for%20able%20adults%2C%20he%20acknowledged%20that%20everyone%20has%20different%20considerations%20and%20advised%20that%20physical%20activity%20should%20be%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714386120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fr17si58_yoga-generic_625x300_29_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fhealth%2Fhow-many-hours-of-physical-activity-for-good-health-what-study-says-5548730%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20optimal%20health%2C%20a%20person's%20ideal%20day%20should%20include%20more%20than%20four%20hours%20of%20physical%20activity%20involving%20exercise%20of%20light%2C%20moderate%20or%20vigourous%20intensity%2C%20and%20at%20least%20eight%20hours%20of%20sleep%2C%20new%20research%20has%20found.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fhealth%2Fhow-many-hours-of-physical-activity-for-good-health-what-study-says-5548730%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fhealth%2Fhow-many-hours-of-physical-activity-for-good-health-what-study-says-5548730%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fhealth%2Fhow-many-hours-of-physical-activity-for-good-health-what-study-says-5548730%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7