red%20standing%20for%20long%20periods%20wouldn't%20work%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20physical%20limitations%20can%20make%20it%20much%20harder%20for%20people%20to%20land%20a%20suitable%20job.%20In%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fdisabl.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabout%2044%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20men%20and%20women%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2025%20and%2054%20with%20a%20disability%20had%20a%20job%2C%20compared%20to%20roughly%2083%25%20of%20people%20without%20a%20disability%2C%20per%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-work-from-home-worth-pay-cut-less-time-off-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erise%20of%20remote%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20helped%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fdisabl.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20disabilities%20find%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20George%20said%20his%20roommate%20has%20health%20issues%20that%20make%20them%20unable%20to%20drive.%20George%20said%20ride-hailing%20provides%20him%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdriving-for-uber-lyft-flexibility-gig-work-doordash-stock-earnings-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enecessary%20flexibility%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20transport%20his%20roommate%20to%20doctor's%20appointments%20and%20to%20and%20from%20their%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20a%20number%20of%20frustrations%20because%20I%20only%20want%20to%20better%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20George%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20because%20of%20the%20situation%20as%20it%20is%2C%20I%20continue%20to%20run%20into%20a%20brick%20wall.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%20said%20he%20sees%20one%20potential%20way%20out%3A%20becoming%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-job-bank-become-truck-driver-pandemic-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etruck%20driver%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20occupation%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fsacramento%2Fnews%2Fnew-study-shows-u-s-is-facing-truck-driver-shortage%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20demand%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20some%20areas%20of%20the%20US.%20The%20job%20could%20pay%20more%20than%20ride-hailing%20%E2%80%94%20the%20median%20driver%20makes%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Foes%2Fcurrent%2Foes533032.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2454%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20year%2C%20per%20the%20BLS%20%E2%80%94%20and%20would%20be%20manageable%20for%20his%20hip.%20If%20George%20pursues%20this%20job%20path%2C%20he%20said%20his%20roommate%20is%20open%20to%20figuring%20out%20an%20alternative%20transportation%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20solution%20could%20come%20with%20some%20challenges%20of%20its%20own.%20For%20one%2C%20George%20said%20the%20training%20costs%20several%20thousand%20dollars%20and%20that%20he'd%20have%20to%20undergo%20several%20weeks%20of%20unpaid%20training%20to%20get%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fschool-bus-driver-shortage-new-york-550000-commercial-drivers-license-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommercial%20driver's%20license%3C%2Fa%3E%20necessary%20for%20the%20job.%20He's%20also%20not%20sure%20he%20can%20afford%20to%20forego%20income%20for%20that%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'd%20have%20to%20save%20money%20to%20be%20able%20to%20help%20my%20roommate%20afford%20things%20while%20I%20was%20away%20from%20home%20and%20not%20earning%20income%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20all%20things%20in%20life%20are%2C%20it's%20complicated%20and%20not%20just%20as%20simple%20as%20making%20the%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20gig%20worker%20willing%20to%20share%20your%20story%20about%20pay%2C%20schedule%2C%20and%20tipping%3F%20Are%20you%20struggling%20to%20find%20a%20better%20job%3F%20If%20so%2C%20reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajzinkula%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejzinkula%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-driving-for-uber-worth-it-declining-pay-more-competition-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714384981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6629090e10dfcda409628ed8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-driving-for-uber-worth-it-declining-pay-more-competition-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Cleveland-based%20Uber%20driver%20shares%20why%20he%20wants%20to%20quit%20ride-hailing%2C%20and%20why%20he's%20not%20sure%20he%20can%20find%20a%20better%20job.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Zinkula)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A134%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-driving-for-uber-worth-it-declining-pay-more-competition-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Exclusive%3A%20Bill%20Gates%2C%20ousted%20for%20misconduct%2C%20is%20still%20pulling%20the%20strings%20at%20Microsoft%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bill%20Gates%20keeps%20track%20of%20all%20the%20businesses%20that%20Microsoft%20is%20involved%20in.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6619a23b1caec1275a6fe39b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BSatya%20and%20the%20entire%20senior%20leadership%20team%20lean%20on%20Gates%20very%20significantly%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20executive.%20%26quot%3BHis%20opinion%20is%20sought%20every%20time%20we%20make%20a%20major%20change.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EAkinbostanci%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20Nobi_Prizue%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20MR.Cole_Photographer%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20Dimitrios%20Kambouris%C2%A0%2F%C2%A0Staff%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20Leon%20Neal%C2%A0%2F%C2%A0Staff%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20NurPhoto%20%2F%20Contributor%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20Abanti%20Chowdhury%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20just%20before%20Microsoft%20forged%20a%20partnership%20with%20a%20then%20relatively%20unknown%20startup%20called%20OpenAI%2C%20Bill%20Gates%20shared%20a%20memo%20with%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella%20and%20a%20small%20group%20of%20the%20company's%20top%20executives.%20A%20new%20world%20order%2C%20Gates%20predicted%2C%20would%20soon%20be%20brought%20on%20by%20what%20he%20called%20%26quot%3BAI%20agents%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20digital%20personal%20assistants%20that%20could%20anticipate%20our%20every%20want%20and%20need.%20These%20agents%20would%20be%20far%20more%20powerful%20than%20Siri%20and%20Alexa%2C%20with%20godlike%20knowledge%20and%20supernatural%20intuition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAgents%20are%20not%20only%20going%20to%20change%20how%20everyone%20interacts%20with%20computers%2C%26quot%3B%20Gates%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20also%20going%20to%20upend%20the%20software%20industry%2C%20bringing%20about%20the%20biggest%20revolution%20in%20computing%20since%20we%20went%20from%20typing%20commands%20to%20tapping%20on%20icons.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20the%20memo%20struck%20those%20who%20read%20it%20as%20far-fetched.%20%26quot%3BIt%20seemed%20super%20futuristic%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Microsoft%20executive%20who%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20said.%20Microsoft%20had%20been%20widely%20mocked%20for%20its%20previous%20attempts%20at%20creating%20personal%20%26quot%3Bagents%2C%26quot%3B%20from%20its%20failed%20Office%20assistant%20Clippy%20to%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-expert-explains-why-microsofts-tay-chatbot-is-so-racist-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eracist%3C%2Fa%3E%20chatbot%2C%20Tay.%20Few%20at%20the%20time%20would%20have%20believed%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20these%20agents%20would%20transform%20Microsoft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20though%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20Gates'%20secret%20correspondence%20anticipated%20Copilot%2C%20the%20artificial-intelligence%20tool%20that%20has%20helped%20propel%20Microsoft%20to%20become%20the%20world's%20most%20valuable%20public%20company.%20Powered%20by%20a%20version%20of%20OpenAI's%20GPT%20large%20language%20model%2C%20Copilot%20debuted%20last%20year%20as%20a%20tool%20within%20Microsoft%20products%20to%20help%20users%20with%20tasks%20such%20as%20preparing%20presentations%20and%20summarizing%20meetings.%20%26quot%3BCopilot%20now%20sounds%20exactly%20like%20what%20he%20wrote%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20executive%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20by%20accident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPublicly%2C%20Gates%20has%20been%20almost%20entirely%20out%20of%20the%20picture%20at%20Microsoft%20since%202021%2C%20following%20allegations%20that%20he%20had%20behaved%20inappropriately%20toward%20female%20employees.%20In%20fact%2C%20Business%20Insider%20has%20learned%2C%20Gates%20has%20been%20quietly%20orchestrating%20much%20of%20Microsoft's%20AI%20revolution%20from%20behind%20the%20scenes.%20Current%20and%20former%20executives%20say%20Gates%20remains%20intimately%20involved%20in%20the%20company's%20operations%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0advising%20on%20strategy%2C%20reviewing%20products%2C%20recruiting%20high-level%20executives%2C%20and%20nurturing%20Microsoft's%20crucial%20relationship%20with%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI.%20In%20early%202023%2C%20when%20Microsoft%20debuted%20a%20version%20of%20its%20search%20engine%20Bing%20turbocharged%20by%20the%20same%20technology%20as%20ChatGPT%2C%20throwing%20down%20the%20gauntlet%20against%20competitors%20like%20Google%2C%20Gates%2C%20executives%20said%2C%20was%20pivotal%20in%20setting%20the%20plan%20in%20motion.%20While%20Nadella%20might%20be%20the%20public%20face%20of%20the%20company's%20AI%20success%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Oz%20who%20built%20the%20yellow-brick%20road%20to%20a%20%243%20trillion%20juggernaut%20%E2%80%94%20Gates%20has%20been%20the%20man%20behind%20the%20curtain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20you%20read%20is%20not%20what's%20happening%20in%20reality%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20Microsoft%20executive%20said.%20%26quot%3BSatya%20and%20the%20entire%20senior%20leadership%20team%20lean%20on%20Gates%20very%20significantly.%20His%20opinion%20is%20sought%20every%20time%20we%20make%20a%20major%20change.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Nadella%20took%20over%20the%20reins%20from%20Steve%20Ballmer%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20Microsoft%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20dinosaur%20of%20the%20computer%20age%20it%20had%20helped%20pioneer.%20Peter%20Thiel%20bashed%20the%20company%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20bet%20against%20technological%20innovation.%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESo%20Nadella%2C%20who%20had%20worked%20at%20Microsoft%20since%201992%2C%20turned%20to%20his%20former%20boss%20for%20help.%20On%20the%20day%20Nadella%20became%20CEO%2C%20he%20asked%20Gates%20to%20spend%2030%25%20of%20his%20time%20as%20a%20technical%20advisor%2C%20in%20part%20to%20help%20motivate%20his%20staff.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20say%2C%20'Hey%2C%20I%20want%20you%20to%20go%20run%20this%20by%20Bill%2C'%20I%20know%20they're%20going%20to%20do%20their%20best%20job%20prepping%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Wired%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20when%20Gates%20stepped%20down%20as%20chair%20of%20Microsoft's%20board%2C%20Nadella%20showered%20him%20with%20praise.%20The%20company%2C%20Nadella%20promised%2C%20would%20%26quot%3Bcontinue%20to%20benefit%20from%20Bill's%20ongoing%20technical%20passion%20and%20advice%20to%20drive%20our%20products%20and%20services%20forward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20year%20later%2C%20Nadella's%20embrace%20of%20Gates%20appeared%20to%20change%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0at%20least%20publicly.%20In%202021%2C%20as%20Gates%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Melinda%2C%20were%20divorcing%2C%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%20that%20Gates%20had%20been%20forced%20to%20step%20down%20as%20the%20company%20investigated%20him%20for%20having%20an%20affair%20with%20an%20employee.%20As%20news%20of%20Gates'%20misconduct%20went%20viral%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbill-gates-melinda-divorce-affairs-bully-womanizer-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20squeaky-clean%20reputation%20he%20and%20his%20public-relations%20team%20had%20meticulously%20crafted%20over%20the%20years%20unraveled%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Several%20female%20employees%20came%20forward%20with%20stories%20of%20Gates%20asking%20them%20out%2C%20and%20his%20meetings%20with%20Jeffrey%20Epstein%2C%20including%20a%20flight%20on%20Epstein's%20private%20jet%2C%20came%20under%20renewed%20scrutiny.%20Suddenly%2C%20Nadella's%20mentor%20had%20become%20his%20greatest%20liability%2C%20and%20he%20and%20Microsoft%20quickly%20distanced%20themselves%20from%20Gates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Microsoft%20of%202021%20is%20very%20different%20from%20the%20Microsoft%20of%202000%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadella%20said%20at%20the%20time.%20%26quot%3BThe%20power%20dynamic%20in%20the%20workplace%20is%20not%20something%20that%20can%20be%20abused%20in%20any%20form.%26quot%3B%20The%20company's%20greatest%20responsibility%2C%20he%20later%20added%2C%20is%20%26quot%3Bcultivating%20a%20culture%20where%20everyone%20is%20empowered%20to%20do%20meaningful%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20among%20the%20people%20whom%20Nadella%20secretly%20empowered%20to%20do%20meaningful%20work%2C%20BI%20has%20learned%2C%20was%20Gates%20himself.%20Rather%20than%20banishing%20him%20from%20the%20company%2C%20Nadella%20continued%20to%20draw%20on%20his%20advice%20and%20expertise%20%E2%80%94%20making%20Gates%20a%20key%20player%20in%20Microsoft's%20efforts%20to%20vie%20for%20dominance%20in%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20common%20lore%20about%20Microsoft's%20marriage%20with%20OpenAI%20is%20that%20it%20was%20brokered%20by%20Kevin%20Scott%2C%20the%20company's%20chief%20technology%20officer.%20Scott%20had%20known%20Altman%20for%20years%2C%20and%20in%20summer%202018%2C%20he%20arranged%20a%20meeting%20between%20Altman%20and%20Nadella.%20Later%20that%20year%2C%20the%20three%20men%20hammered%20out%20an%20initial%20deal%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20is%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20lost%20in%20that%20origin%20story%20is%20that%20Gates%20had%20been%20regularly%20meeting%20with%20OpenAI%20since%202016.%20Ever%20since%20he%20published%20%26quot%3BThe%20Road%20Ahead%26quot%3B%20in%201995%2C%20Gates%20had%20been%20dreaming%20of%20a%20world%20in%20which%20everyone%20would%20navigate%20the%20internet%20using%20software%20that%20would%20%26quot%3Bhave%20a%20personality%20you'll%20be%20able%20to%20talk%20to%20in%20one%20form%20or%20another%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20would%20%26quot%3Blearn%20about%20your%20requirements%20and%20preferences%20in%20much%20the%20way%20that%20a%20human%20assistant%20does.%26quot%3B%20Under%20Gates'%20leadership%2C%20Microsoft%20had%20launched%20several%20primitive%20and%20widely%20ridiculed%20versions%20of%20agents%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0from%20Rover%2C%20a%20cartoon%20dog%20that%20guided%20you%20through%20Windows%2095%2C%20to%20Clippy%2C%20the%20most%20hated%20paperclip%20of%20all%20time.%20Now%2C%20it%20seemed%2C%20OpenAI%20might%20offer%20Microsoft%20a%20way%20to%20help%20forge%20the%20AI%20future%20that%20Gates%20had%20long%20envisioned.%20After%20the%20two%20companies%20formed%20their%20partnership%2C%20OpenAI's%20leaders%20conducted%20regular%20presentations%20for%20Gates%20at%20his%2066%2C000-square-foot%20mansion%20in%20Washington%2C%20keeping%20him%20apprised%20of%20critical%20benchmarks%20and%20significant%20obstacles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Gates%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20who%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20turning%20OpenAI%20and%20Microsoft%20into%20a%20power%20couple.%20In%20mid-2022%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0two%20years%20after%20he%20was%20ousted%20from%20the%20board%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0he%20privately%20challenged%20Altman%20and%20OpenAI%20to%20create%20a%20model%20capable%20of%20passing%20an%20Advanced%20Placement%20biology%20exam.%20Gates%20didn't%20think%20it%20could%20be%20done.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAltman%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOpenAI%20debuted%20GPT-4%20for%20the%20first%20time%20outside%20the%20company%20at%20Gates'%20house%20in%20August%202022%20during%20a%20dinner%3B%20Nadella%20was%20among%20the%20guests.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhen%20it%20aced%20the%20test%2C%20Gates%20was%20shocked%2C%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20stunning%20demo%20I've%20ever%20seen%20in%20my%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demo%20prompted%20Gates%20to%20write%20another%20memo%20%E2%80%94%20what%20one%20former%20executive%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Ethe%3C%2Fem%3E%20memo%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20spelling%20out%20how%20Microsoft%20should%20use%20GPT-4.%20Gates%20stressed%20that%20the%20large%20language%20model%2C%20trained%20on%20the%20entirety%20of%20the%20public%20internet%2C%20could%20finally%20usher%20in%20the%20era%20of%20personal%20agents.%20%26quot%3BThink%20of%20it%20as%20a%20digital%20personal%20assistant%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20a%20version%20of%20that%20memo%20later%20posted%20on%20his%20blog.%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20see%20your%20latest%20emails%2C%20know%20about%20the%20meetings%20you%20attend%2C%20read%20what%20you%20read%2C%20and%20read%20the%20things%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20bother%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20two%20executives%2C%20Gates'%20words%20were%20treated%20as%20gospel%2C%20helping%20spark%20Microsoft's%20push%20to%20take%20the%20lead%20in%20the%20AI%20arms%20race.%20Soon%20after%20Gates'%20dinner%2C%20Nadella%20hosted%20a%20meeting%20on%20Microsoft's%20campus%2C%20where%20he%20challenged%20the%20teams%20to%20incorporate%20AI%20into%20search%2C%20cybersecurity%2C%20and%20its%20Microsoft%20365%20suite%20of%20business%20applications%2C%20which%20includes%20Word%20and%20Outlook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20the%20following%20year%2C%20Microsoft%20introduced%20a%20new%20version%20of%20its%20beleaguered%20search%20engine%2C%20Bing%20%E2%80%94%20now%20turbocharged%20with%20a%20GPT-enabled%20agent%20that%20would%20later%20be%20named%20Copilot.%20Almost%20overnight%2C%20thanks%20to%20Gates'%20maneuvering%2C%20Microsoft%20had%20transformed%20Bing%20from%20a%20search%20engine%20on%20life%20support%20to%20an%20AI-powered%20tool%20that%20had%20a%20chance%20to%20give%20Google%20a%20run%20for%20its%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202023%2C%20Microsoft%20held%20an%20event%20at%20its%20headquarters%20similar%20to%20a%20Steve%20Jobs%20iPhone%20launch.%20Nadella%2C%20beaming%2C%20declared%20war%20on%20Google.%20Gates%20did%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20in%20attendance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Gates%20remains%20close%20with%20Altman%2C%20who%20visits%20his%20home%20a%20few%20times%20a%20year%2C%20and%20OpenAI%20seeks%20his%20counsel%20on%20developments.%20There's%20a%20%26quot%3Btight%20coupling%26quot%3B%20between%20Gates%20and%20OpenAI%2C%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20relationship%20said.%20%26quot%3BSam%20and%20Bill%20are%20good%20friends.%20OpenAI%20takes%20his%20opinion%20and%20consult%20overall%20seriously.%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20spokesperson%20Kayla%20Wood%20confirmed%20OpenAI%20continues%20to%20meet%20with%20Gates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20fall%2C%20Nadella%20and%20Microsoft%20scrambled%20to%20quell%20the%20chaos%20when%20OpenAI's%20board%20abruptly%20fired%20Altman.%20Frank%20Shaw%2C%20a%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20if%20Gates%20was%20speaking%20with%20Altman%2C%20it%20was%20not%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20company.%20%26quot%3BBill%20is%20not%20at%20Microsoft%20and%20not%20involved%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Shaw%20told%20BI%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20five-day%20fracas%20that%20followed%2C%20Gates%20%E2%80%94%20with%20his%20own%20recent%20experience%20with%20an%20ouster%20%E2%80%94%20reached%20out%20to%20Altman%20to%20offer%20support%20as%20he%20negotiated%20a%20return%20to%20the%20leadership%20of%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20insiders%20say%20Gates'%20sway%20at%20Microsoft%20extends%20far%20beyond%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExecutives%20from%20across%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0including%20its%20business-applications%20boss%2C%20Charles%20Lamanna%3B%20its%20chief%20scientist%2C%20Jaime%20Teevan%3B%20its%20Teams%20chat-app%20boss%2C%20Jeff%20Teper%3B%20and%20its%20head%20of%20cybersecurity%2C%20Charlie%20Bell%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0meet%20regularly%20with%20Gates%20to%20review%20products.%20He's%20also%20personally%20involved%20in%20recruiting%20and%20retaining%20important%20executives%20for%20Microsoft.%20%26quot%3BGates%20is%20very%20involved%20with%20product%20reviews%20and%20one-on-ones%20with%20executives%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20executive%20said.%20Last%20year%2C%20Gates%20told%20Forbes%20he%20spent%20about%2010%25%20of%20his%20time%20in%20Redmond%2C%20Washington%2C%20advising%20Microsoft%20on%20product%20road%20maps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGates%20over%20years%20has%20also%20pushed%20Microsoft%20to%20be%20more%20consumer-focused%2C%20despite%20many%20consumer%20technology%20failures.%20In%20March%2C%20many%20observers%20were%20shocked%20when%20the%20company%20announced%20it%20was%20hiring%20Mustafa%20Suleyman%2C%20who%20cofounded%20DeepMind%20and%20spent%20many%20years%20at%20Google%2C%20to%20lead%20a%20new%20consumer-AI%20organization.%20%26quot%3BBill%20G.%20thinks%20the%20major%20opportunity%20is%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20insider%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20new%20consumer-AI%20organization%2C%20that%20looks%20like%20Bill's%20influence%20on%20Satya.%26quot%3B%20Shaw%20said%20Gates%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20hiring%20Suleyman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20is%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20the%20perception%20that%20Gates%20has%20been%20kept%20at%20a%20distance%20ever%20since%20he%20was%20ousted%20from%20the%20board.%20Gates%2C%20who%20has%20continued%20to%20keep%20a%20low%20profile%2C%20has%20emerged%20from%20the%20scandal%20largely%20unscathed%3B%20today%2C%20the%20allegations%20of%20his%20misconduct%20aren't%20even%20mentioned%20in%20his%20Wikipedia%20entry.%20The%20Microsoft%20of%202024%2C%20it%20appears%2C%20is%20not%20as%20different%20from%20the%20Microsoft%20of%202021%20as%20Nadella%20would%20have%20everyone%20believe.%20Gates%20is%20not%20gone%2C%20but%20his%20checkered%20past%20has%20been%20largely%20forgotten.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShaw%20said%20there%20hadn't%20been%20any%20substantial%20changes%20in%20Gates'%20role%20as%20a%20technical%20advisor%20since%20he%20left%20the%20board%20in%202020.%20Gates%20declined%20an%20interview%20request%20and%20his%20representative%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENear%20the%20end%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Road%20Ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20Gates%20got%20existential.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20little%20scary%20that%20as%20computer%20technology%20has%20moved%20ahead%2C%20there's%20never%20been%20a%20leader%20from%20one%20era%20who%20was%20also%20a%20leader%20in%20the%20next%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20lamented%20at%20the%20ripe%20age%20of%2039.%20%26quot%3BSo%20from%20a%20historical%20perspective%2C%20I%20guess%20Microsoft%20is%20disqualified%20from%20leading%20in%20the%20highway%20era%20of%20the%20Information%20Age.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20middle-aged%20Gates%20revealed%20his%20true%20ambition%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20defy%20historical%20tradition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20approaching%2070%2C%20Gates%20is%20still%20defying%20history%20%E2%80%94%20this%20time%20from%20behind%20the%20scenes.%20And%20if%20the%20revived%20fortunes%20of%20Microsoft%20are%20any%20indication%2C%20he%20appears%20to%20be%20winning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%