22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D347476%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20a%20time%20when%20his%20friends%20secured%20government%20jobs%2C%20Bhavesh%20Chaudhary%20had%20no%20direction%20in%20life.%20Today%20he%20has%20established%20a%20multi-crore%20brand%20called%20Kasutam%2C%20selling%20homemade%20A2%20bilona%20ghee.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A61%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F347476%2Fkasutam-bilona-ghee-business-haryana-man-bhavesh-chaudhary-sells-a2-ghee-earns-lakhs-per-months%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20a%20Gardener%20Grows%20Mango%2C%20Chikoo%2C%20Orange%20%26amp%3B%2014%20Other%20Fruits%20In%20Crates%20On%20Her%20Terrace%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EJayanti%20Sahoo%E2%80%99s%20day%20starts%20with%20harvesting%20guavas%2C%20mulberries%2C%20chikoos%2C%20and%20pomegranates%20from%20her%20lush%20green%20rooftop%20garden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20days%2C%20people%20put%20chemicals%20to%20artificially%20ripen%20fruits.%20Fruits%20are%20coated%20with%20wax%20and%20chemicals%20to%20make%20them%20glossy.%20We%20are%20blessed%20to%20eat%20fruits%20that%20are%20completely%20chemical-free%20and%20organically%20grown.%20Our%20fruits%20are%20comparatively%20sweeter%20than%20those%20available%20in%20the%20market%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%20as%20I%20prepare%20to%20ask%20Jayanti%20all%20about%20her%20journey%20that%20led%20to%20her%20turning%20her%20very%20home%20into%20a%20mini%20jungle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20350%20sq%20ft%20terrace%2C%20along%20with%20her%20three-storey%20house%20covering%20a%20total%20area%20of%20around%201%2C500%20sq%20ft%2C%20is%20thriving%20with%20a%20diverse%20array%20of%20plants.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20vacant%20place%20left%20in%20my%20home%20where%20I%20could%20add%20more%20pots.%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20more%20space%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20laughs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayanti%2C%20now%2056%20years%20old%2C%20narrates%20that%20it%20was%20during%20her%20childhood%20she%20took%20a%20keen%20interest%20in%20gardening.%20Growing%20up%20in%20Bhubaneswar%2C%20Odisha%2C%20a%20young%20Jayanti%20lived%20along%20with%20her%20six%20siblings%20and%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20of%20us%20lived%20in%20a%20small%20home.%20My%20father%20would%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F278952%2Fkerala-gardener-grows-135-fruit-trees-in-plastic-drums-on-terrace-shares-tips%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrow%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20%3C%2Fa%3Ein%20the%20backyard%20and%20we%20helped%20him%20in%20gardening.%20We%20would%20be%20very%20excited%20to%20fetch%20water%20from%20the%20well%20and%20water%20all%20the%20plants%20together.%20He%20would%20teach%20us%20how%20to%20take%20care%20of%20plants.%20It%20was%20fun%20to%20be%20in%20the%20garden%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20piqued%20her%20interest%20in%20gardening%20and%20her%20desire%20to%20create%20a%20small%20garden%20of%20her%20own.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20father%20would%20not%20grow%20flowering%20plants.%20But%20I%20always%20desired%20to%20grow%20roses%20and%20%3Cem%3Erajanigandha%20%3C%2Fem%3E(tuberose).%20So%2C%20when%20I%20grew%20up%2C%20I%20set%20up%20a%20small%20garden%20of%20roses%20and%20other%20flowers.%20My%20father%20would%20bring%20guests%20to%20my%20garden%20and%20proudly%20say%20that%20this%20was%20his%20daughter%E2%80%99s%20garden%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-4-1713363464.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jayanti%20grows%20fruits%20like%20guavas%2C%20pomegranates%2C%20oranges%2C%20mangoes%2C%20and%20chikoos%20on%20her%20terrace.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-4-1713363464.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-4-1713363464-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-4-1713363464-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-4-1713363464-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-4-1713363464-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-347569%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EJayanti%20grows%20fruits%20like%20guavas%2C%20pomegranates%2C%20oranges%2C%20mangoes%2C%20and%20chikoos%20on%20her%20terrace.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201989%2C%20when%20the%20BSc%20graduate%20got%20married%2C%20she%20took%20her%20gardening%20interest%20to%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20home%20along%20with%20her%20clothes%20and%20jewellery!%20%E2%80%9CMy%20husband%E2%80%99s%20place%20did%20not%20have%20many%20plants%20except%20bananas%20and%20drumsticks.%20I%20started%20planting%20flowering%20plants%20like%20marigolds%20and%20bougainvillaea%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20Jayanti%20visited%20an%20offline%20exhibition%20where%20she%20was%20introduced%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20grafting.%20%E2%80%9CI%20saw%20trees%20like%20mangoes%2C%20oranges%2C%20and%20chikoos%20were%20grown%20in%20a%20pot!%20Before%20this%2C%20I%20had%20only%20seen%20these%20trees%20on%20large%20farms.%20Unlike%20them%2C%20these%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F338660%2Fhow-to-grow-fruits-on-terrace-gardening-tips-visakhapatnam-woman-wins-award%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efruit%20trees%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewere%20just%205%20to%208%20feet%20in%20height%2C%20but%20they%20were%20yielding%20fruits.%20I%20was%20eager%20to%20grow%20such%20fruit%20trees%20at%20my%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayanti%E2%80%99s%20quest%20led%20her%20to%20create%20a%20mini%20jungle%20on%20her%20terrace%20and%20in%20her%20house.%20Along%20with%20seasonal%20vegetables%20like%20brinjals%2C%20cucumber%2C%20okra%2C%20spinach%2C%20tomatoes%2C%20radish%2C%20and%20more%2C%20she%20cultivates%2017%20kinds%20of%20fruit%20trees%20%E2%80%94%20including%20guavas%2C%20pomegranates%2C%20oranges%2C%20cherries%2C%20star%20fruit%2C%20white%20jamun%2C%20mulberries%2C%20apple%20bear%2C%20water%20apple%2C%20mangoes%2C%20and%20chikoos%20on%20her%20terrace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20all%2C%20I%20grow%20flowers%2C%20fruits%2C%20and%20vegetables%20in%20my%20house%20spread%20across%20a%20total%20area%20of%20about%201%2C500%20square%20feet%20including%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F302262%2Fpatna-couple-grow-fruit-trees-plants-organic-vegetables-on-terrace-garden%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eterrace%20and%20balconies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20reiterates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20article%2C%20Jayanti%20shares%20secret%20tips%20and%20techniques%20that%20have%20helped%20her%20to%20grow%20fruits%20in%20her%20rooftop%20garden%2C%20which%20can%20help%20you%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1713363481.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jayanti%20grows%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20including%20chikoo%2C%20tomatoes%2C%20and%20brinjals%20on%20her%20350%20sq%20ft%20terrace.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1713363481.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1713363481-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1713363481-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1713363481-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1713363481-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-347570%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EJayanti%20grows%20fruits%20and%20vegetables%20including%20chikoo%2C%20tomatoes%2C%20and%20brinjals%20on%20her%20350%20sq%20ft%20terrace.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGrow%20your%20own%20fruits%20with%20these%208%20tips%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Place%20the%20fruit%20trees%20strategically%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20Jayanti%2C%20urban%20gardeners%20should%20first%20ensure%20a%20proper%20drainage%20system%20on%20the%20terrace%20so%20that%20it%20does%20not%20absorb%20excess%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSecondly%2C%20keep%20your%20pots%20such%20that%20they%20are%20placed%20above%20the%20beams%20and%20walls%20of%20the%20rooms%20that%20are%20below%20the%20terrace.%20This%20will%20ensure%20that%20the%20weight%20of%20trees%20is%20balanced%20and%20the%20foundation%20of%20the%20house%20does%20not%20get%20damaged%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Upcycle%20discarded%20fish%20crates%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20large%20pots%2C%20Jayanti%20plants%20fruits%20in%20fish%20crates%20of%2027*17*12%20inches.%20%E2%80%9CI%20purchase%20discarded%20fish%20crates%20at%20lower%20prices%20in%20the%20fish%20market.%20I%20make%20holes%20at%20its%20bottom%20and%20then%20add%20the%20soil%20mixture.%20These%20fish%20crates%20are%20very%20sturdy.%20I%20am%20still%20using%20fish%20crates%20that%20I%20bought%2020%20years%20ago%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-3-1713363525.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Instead%20of%20large%20pots%2C%20Jayanti%20plants%20fruits%20in%20fish%20crates.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-3-1713363525.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-3-1713363525-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-3-1713363525-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-3-1713363525-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-3-1713363525-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-347572%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EInstead%20of%20large%20pots%2C%20Jayanti%20plants%20fruits%20in%20fish%20crates.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Prefer%20grafted%20saplings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEarlier%2C%20people%20would%20grow%20fruits%20from%20seeds%2C%20but%20this%20process%20takes%20five%20to%20seven%20years%20to%20give%20yield.%20In%20contrast%2C%20grafted%20plants%20give%20produce%20within%20a%20year.%20Initially%2C%20I%20plant%20the%20sapling%20into%20a%20small%20pot%20of%20say%2015%20inches%20before%20transferring%20it%20into%20the%20fish%20crates.%20After%20about%20a%20year%2C%20the%20plant%20will%20be%20root-bound%20enough%20to%20be%20shifted%20into%20a%20comparatively%20large%20fish%20crate%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Prepare%20the%20right%20soil%20mixture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayanti%20says%20preparing%20a%20perfect%20soil%20mix%20for%20pots%20is%20an%20extremely%20important%20step%20as%20its%20components%20act%20as%20true%20boosters%20for%20fruit%20trees%20that%20are%20typically%20grown%20in%20large%20farmland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20you%20grow%20fruit%20trees%20on%20the%20terrace%2C%20you%20should%20prepare%20a%20lightweight%20potting%20mixture.%20Mix%2030%20percent%20garden%20soil%20with%2030%20percent%20cow%20dung%20compost%2C%2030%20percent%20cocopeat%2C%205%20percent%20of%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%3C%2Fem%3E%20(cake)%20powder%2C%20and%205%20percent%20of%20bonemeal%20powder.%20Before%20transferring%20the%20mix%20into%20the%20pot%2C%20place%20a%20thick%20layer%20(4-5%20inches)%20of%20dried%20leaves%20on%20the%20pot%20which%20will%20turn%20into%20compost%20later%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Add%20liquid%20fertiliser%20to%20boost%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20grown%20on%20a%20farm%2C%20trees%20take%20nutrients%20from%20the%20soil%2C%20but%20when%20we%20grow%20them%20in%20pots%2C%20we%20need%20to%20provide%20them%20with%20additional%20nutrients%20regularly%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Jayanti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jayanti%E2%80%99s%20techniques%20have%20helped%20her%20get%20sufficient%20fruits%20for%20the%20past%20three%20decades.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-1-1713363511-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-347571%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EJayanti%E2%80%99s%20techniques%20have%20helped%20her%20get%20sufficient%20fruits%20for%20the%20past%20three%20decades.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTo%20provide%20additional%20nutrients%2C%20take%201%20kg%20mustard%20cake%20and%20250%20grams%20of%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%20%3C%2Fem%3Epowder%20and%20mix%20it%20in%205%20litres%20of%20water.%20Stir%20it%20and%20then%20keep%20it%20under%20shade%20for%20five%20days.%20Mix%201%20litre%20of%20this%20liquid%20fertiliser%20in%2010%20litres%20of%20water%20and%20give%20the%20diluted%20fertiliser%20to%20the%20plant%20every%2015%20days.%20This%20liquid%20fertiliser%20helps%20boost%20the%20flowering%20and%20fruiting%20in%20the%20trees%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20Deal%20with%20pests%20early%20on%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayanti%20regularly%20sprays%20neem%20oil%20to%20control%20pest%20and%20insect%20attacks.%20%E2%80%9CUsually%2C%20I%20handpick%20bugs%20from%20plants%20and%20remove%20leaves%20where%20they%20lay%20eggs.%20I%20have%20also%20used%20sticky%20fly%20traps%20to%20control%20fruit%20flies%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Know%20when%20to%20prune%20trees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20keep%20getting%20good%20yields%2C%20Jayanti%20advises%20urban%20gardeners%20to%20keep%20pruning%20trees%20every%20two%20to%20three%20years.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20avoid%20pruning%2C%20then%20you%E2%80%99ll%20start%20getting%20fruits%20that%20are%20smaller%20in%20size.%20Pruning%20helps%20maintain%20tree%20size%20and%20maximise%20fruit%20quality%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Provide%20additional%20nutrients%20for%20rootbound%20trees%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20three%20to%20four%20years%2C%20urban%20gardeners%20should%20dig%20out%20a%20thick%20layer%20of%20soil%20(say%203-4%20inches)%20and%20replace%20it%20with%20cow%20dung%20compost%2C%20bonemeal%2C%20and%20neem%20%3Cem%3Ekhali%3C%2Fem%3E%20powder.%20Place%20a%20thin%20layer%20of%20soil%20above%20this%20and%20then%20water%20the%20soil.%20This%20will%20help%20you%20get%20good-sized%20fruits%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJayanti%E2%80%99s%20techniques%20have%20helped%20her%20get%20sufficient%20fruits%20for%20the%20past%20three%20decades.%20She%20now%20eagerly%20awaits%20to%20harvest%20mangoes%20from%20her%20garden!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20homemaker%2C%20gardening%20is%20more%20than%20a%20fun%20hobby.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20brings%20me%20immense%20mental%20peace%20and%20contentment.%20It%20is%20part%20of%20my%20everyday%20routine.%20My%20entire%20day%20goes%20by%20taking%20care%20of%20their%20nutrients%20and%20protecting%20them%20from%20diseases%20and%20pests.%20I%20raise%20these%20trees%20like%20my%20children%2C%E2%80%9D%20smiles%20Jayanti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3B%20All%20photos%3A%20Jayanti%20Sahoo.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714111642000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2FJayanti-Sahoo-4-1713363464.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D347565%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Odisha's%20Jayanti%20Sahoo%20grows%2017%20types%20of%20fruits%20including%20guavas%2C%20pomegranates%2C%20oranges%2C%20white%20jamun%2C%20mangoes%2C%20and%20chikoos%20on%20her%20350%20sq%20ft%20terrace%20garden.%20With%20her%20eight%20secret%20tips%20and%20techniques%2C%20you%20too%20can%20grow%20fruits%20at%20home.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%